1.A good nutritional plan will ensure the right kind of growth and development.

2.Healthy food habits learnt during childhood will ensure that your child will have a healthier life as an adult. Studies have shown that adults who had a nutritionally balanced childhood have lesser instances of high cholesterol or high blood pressure. These individuals also have lesser chances of developing diabetes, heart disease, and cancer

3. With good nutrition, many diseases can be kept at bay. Conditions like iron deficiency, dental cavities, and osteoporosis can be avoided to a large extent.
